Judges 5-9 <t>My heart goes out to the commanders of Israel </t><t>who <f>ⓛ</f>offered themselves willingly among the people. </t><t>Bless the LORD. </t>
Judges 5-10 <pb/><t>“Tell of it, <f>ⓜ</f>you who ride on white donkeys, </t><t>you who sit on rich carpets <f>[2]</f> </t><t>and you who walk by the way.</t>
Judges 5-11 <t>To the sound of musicians <f>[3]</f> at the watering places, </t><t>there they repeat the righteous triumphs of the LORD, </t><t>the righteous triumphs of his villagers in Israel. </t> <pb/><t>“Then down to the gates marched the people of the LORD. </t>
Judges 5-12 <pb/><t><f>ⓝ</f> “Awake, awake, Deborah! </t><t>Awake, awake, break out in a song! </t><t>Arise, Barak, <f>ⓞ</f>lead away your captives, </t><t>O son of Abinoam.</t>
Judges 5-13 <t>Then down marched the remnant of the noble; </t><t>the people of the LORD marched down for me against the mighty.</t>
Judges 5-14 <t>From <f>ⓟ</f>Ephraim their root <f>ⓠ</f>they marched down into the valley, <f>[4]</f> </t><t>following you, Benjamin, with your kinsmen; </t><t>from <f>ⓡ</f>Machir marched down the commanders, </t><t>and from Zebulun those who bear the lieutenant's <f>[5]</f> staff;</t>
